# =============================================================================
# VR SUPERMARKET EYE-TRACKING PIPELINE
# Seeing Through Sensory Overload — FPN, Maastricht University
# =============================================================================
#
# WHAT THIS SCRIPT DOES
#   Converts raw VR task + eye-tracking files into a JASP-ready CSV.
#   One row per participant (15 rows total). All three conditions are
#   represented as column groups within that row.
#
# HOW TO READ THIS DOCUMENT
#   1. CONFIGURATION      — all tunable constants, lists, mappings
#   2. FILE INGESTION     — find, parse, load raw files
#   3. DATA CLEANING      — flag invalid samples (never delete)
#   4. GAZE KINEMATICS    — Euler → velocity → acceleration → smoothing
#   5. EVENT DETECTION    — label every sample: fixation / saccade / excluded
#   6. FIXATION METRICS   — aggregate fixation events → attentional DVs
#   7. TASK PERFORMANCE   — compute accuracy and completion time
#   8. OUTPUT             — assemble and write results.csv
#   9. ORCHESTRATION      — run pipeline for one or all participants
#  10. MENU               — user-facing interface
#
# PIPELINE IN ONE PARAGRAPH
#   Files are found and parsed by participant/condition from the filename.
#   The eye file is loaded (~9500 rows, ~16ms apart) and cleaned: tracker-loss
#   and teleportation samples are flagged. Timestamps are aligned to the eye
#   file's origin. Gaze direction (Euler angles) is converted to unit vectors;
#   angular displacement between consecutive samples gives velocity (°/s).
#   Velocity is smoothed (Savitzky-Golay), then an adaptive threshold
#   (Nyström & Holmqvist, 2010) separates fixations from saccades/glissades.
#   Glissades are merged into saccades. Fixations shorter than 100ms are
#   dropped. Each surviving fixation is assigned an object label (majority
#   vote) and classified as relevant, irrelevant, or neither (nothing).
#   Per-condition attentional metrics are computed (fixation ratio, counts,
#   durations, saccade rate). Task performance is computed from the grab log
#   (accuracy, penalty score, completion time). All three conditions are
#   combined into one row per participant and written to results.csv.
#
# KEY DVs
#   Objective performance : correct_picks / 7
#   Penalty score         : (correct - incorrect) / 7     ← wider spread
#   Fixation ratio        : relevant / (relevant + irrelevant + neither)
#   Saccade rate          : saccades / second
#
# OUTPUT STRUCTURE (one row per participant, columns grouped by condition)
#   participant_id
#   sps_score                                        ← baseline, measured once
#   low_performance_score,    low_penalty_score,     low_grab_accuracy,
#   low_completion_time_s,    low_fixation_ratio,    low_saccade_rate,
#   low_n_saccades,           low_fixation_time_relevant_ms,
#   low_fixation_time_irrelevant_ms,
#   low_n_fixations_relevant, low_n_fixations_irrelevant,
#   low_mean_fixation_dur_relevant_ms,
#   low_mean_fixation_dur_irrelevant_ms,
#   low_post_fatigue,         low_perceived_overload,
#   low_perceived_performance
#   ... same columns repeated for medium_ and high_
#
# FUNCTIONS (in order)
#   INGESTION       find_file_pairs, parse_filename, load_task_file, load_eye_file
#   CLEANING        detect_tracker_loss, detect_teleportation, align_timestamps
#   KINEMATICS      euler_to_unit_vector, compute_angular_displacement,
#                   compute_velocity, compute_acceleration, smooth_velocity
#   DETECTION       compute_adaptive_threshold, classify_samples,
#                   apply_fixation_duration_filter
#   METRICS         assign_fixation_objects, classify_fixation_relevance,
#                   compute_eye_metrics
#   PERFORMANCE     compute_task_performance
#   OUTPUT          build_output_row, write_results
#   ORCHESTRATION   process_pair, run_all, run_one, preview_pairs, inspect_one
#   MENU            menu, get_data_dir, get_output_path
#
# OPEN QUESTIONS
#   - Confirm timestamp unit (seconds vs milliseconds)
#
# =============================================================================

